I saw your post on the succesfull vox raid and the appropriate groups and stratagey, and I was wondering if you would be so kind as to post the same for a naggy raid? Thanks.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvumil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vumil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Lich</span><br>  Posts: 1040<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/28/01 1:56:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nillon Can ya Please Help Me W/ Some Info?</span><hr size=1> 47+<br>
<br>
6 Ideal groups would be...<br>
<br>
tank 1: cleric, cleric, melee, melee, melee, bard<br>
tank 2: cleric, cleric, melee, melee, melee, bard<br>
tank 3: cleric, cleric, melee, melee, melee, bard<br>
caster/tank group: cleric, cleric, melee, melee, melee, bard or... <br>
healer, wizard, wizard, wizard, wizard, healer<br>
(you will most likely have a mix here)<br>
<br>
caster 1: healer, wizard, wizard, wizard, wizard, healer<br>
caster 2: healer, wizard, wizard, wizard, wizard, healer<br>
<br>
If it was necessary you could add a 7th group, or if you have a good enough raid crew you can do it with 24 or 30.<br>
<br>
<br>
Substitute druids for clerics, shamans for wizards.. of course you're going to have to group the enchanters/necros somewhere in a few of those wizard spots or in a mixed caster/tank group.  Mages and druids can't nuke Nagafen.  Mage damage shield adds +fr, so make sure at least all your heavy tanks and clerics get it just before charge.  Ideal resists are 150+ magic and fire resists.<br>
<br>
Send in your heavy tank groups, wait 5 seconds or so, send in any remaining tank groups... when Nag is at 60% or so send in the nukers.  If you have extra healers have them stand just outside the door and have tanks back off for heals there.. they can also heal anyone that is feared.<br>
<br>
For buffs put up 3-4 dummy buffs then hp buffs, rune and MR.. I suggest DMF as the first buff since they can cancel it(if you have a bard cancel it so bard song can be the top buff, it will refresh after it is dispelled that way).<br>
<br>
<br>
I know I missed something, but this is just a quick throw together strat...  If you have any further questions just ask, I'm sure I can answer them. <p><br><font face="Arial" size="-2">Vumil Darksoul<br>
